OL,6,FFor home insurance, the highest rate
OL,7,Fin the Which? study was from Co-op
OL,8,FInsurance. Which? found that customers
OL,9,Fpay between 31.31% to 34.75% APR on
OL,10,Fmonthly payments.
OL,12,FThe average across the providers that
OL,13,Fcharge a rate and disclosed it was 23%.
OL,15,FCo-op Insurance works with partners to
OL,16,Fprovide insurance cover ` and it said
OL,17,Fit is looking to reduce rates where
OL,18,Fpossible. It added that it chose to
OL,19,Fshare its rates with Which? as it is
OL,20,Fcommitted to transparency.
