OL,6,FBut Which? argued that the risk to
OL,7,Finsurers is lower than for credit card
OL,8,Fproviders, because the credit being
OL,9,Foffered is directly linked to the sale
OL,10,Fof the insurance policy and non-
OL,11,Fpayment by customers can lead to the
OL,12,Fcancellation of the policy.
OL,14,FSince January 2022, motor and home
OL,15,Finsurers have been required to provide
OL,16,Ffair value on their products and those
OL,17,Frequirements have been further
OL,18,Fstrengthened by the introduction of
OL,19,Fthe Financial Conduct Authority
OL,20,F(FCA)'s Consumer Duty last year.
